# Chaos TD Rules

1. Read the active task and only its Required Reading.
2. Do not implement deferred features.
3. `packages/game-core` must not import Phaser, DOM, Canvas, WebSocket, LocalStorage or audio.
4. Never use `Math.random()`, `Date.now()`, timers or render delta as game-rule input.
5. Use integer ticks and integer fixed-point values for rule state.
6. The client submits commands; it must not directly mutate authoritative simulation state.
7. Do not duplicate game-data values in UI or scenes.
8. Prefer data-oriented serializable state over per-content inheritance classes.
9. Add or update tests before implementing new behavior.
10. Do not delete or weaken tests to make CI pass.
11. Do not use broad `any`, `as unknown as`, empty stubs or TODOs to claim completion.
12. Do not add frameworks or major dependencies unless the task or accepted ADR permits it.
13. Do not change an accepted ADR silently.
14. Do not modify unrelated files without explaining why.
15. Run the exact verification commands required by the task.
16. A task is not done unless lint, typecheck, required tests and build pass.
17. If specs conflict, follow `docs/13_SOURCE_OF_TRUTH.md`.
18. If ambiguity remains, report `SPEC_BLOCKER` with at most two minimal options; complete all unblocked work.
19. Keep changes reviewable; do not prebuild future empty directory trees.
20. Update documentation when public contracts or authoritative behavior changes.
